# Project Storage Boundary

All files specific to this Red Alert 2 NAS project must stay under:

`/volume2/Data/App_Development/ra2-lan-party`

Do not create, mount, sync, log, cache, or document project-specific files directly under `/volume2/Data/App_Development` or any other NAS location.

Use project subdirectories such as:

- `/volume2/Data/App_Development/ra2-lan-party/project`
- `/volume2/Data/App_Development/ra2-lan-party/assets`
- `/volume2/Data/App_Development/ra2-lan-party/prefixes`
- `/volume2/Data/App_Development/ra2-lan-party/logs`
- `/volume2/Data/App_Development/ra2-lan-party/tls`

The only exception is truly shared tooling or dependencies intended for multiple projects, such as a shared Python package or cross-project dependency. Those may live under `/volume2/Data/App_Development` when they are not RA2-project-specific.
